sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1791002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Low RBS expressing MS2 Coat protein ribozyme affinity purification (RAP)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is an amalgamation of several biobricks an MS2 coat protein, an MS2 binding domain and the theophylline ribozyme (BBa_K1791000)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: low RBS expressing MS2 Coat protein ribozyme affinity purification (RAP). This part utilizes the expression of C-terminal 6X His tagged fusion MS2 coat protein under a T7 promoter and a low efficiency shine dalgarno sequence for expression of MS2. Downstream there is a T7 promoter followed by a theophylline ribozyme and a MS2 apatamer at the 3' end. Co-expression of the two modules results in MS2 binding to the 3' end of the theophylline ribozyme transcript allowing for the MS2-RNA purification by nickel affinity chromatography. The RNA can be eluted from the complex by the addition of theophylline.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to consider MS2 expression levels relative to the theophylline ribozyme transcript and assessed how this affects total RNA yield. In order to test this we developed a second part with increased MS2 expression (BBa_K1791001)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Graeme Glaister

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Medium RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-1" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS.

Contact info for this part: Brian Cho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1791003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 6X end terminally His tagged MS2 coat protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: MS2 coat protein can be easily purified via a nickel sepharose purification if this part is used downstream of a promoter and RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Graeme Glaister

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1791005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter fused with a theophylline inducible ribozyme (aptazyme)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Win, M.N., Smolke C.D. 2007 and BBa_I719005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was developed in order to increase the sequence space flexibility in dsRNA generated using BBa_K1791001 and BBa_K1791002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: by changing the T7 promoter sequence (BBa_I719005) slightly after the GGG trinulceotide we get an increase in the potential for generating RNA with our composite parts BBa_K1791001 and BBa_K1791002.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Graeme Glaister

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1791006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is an aptamer designed to bind MS2 coat protein upon transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Had to test that it optimally binds to MS2 coat protein in vivo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Graeme Glaister

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no addtional design features were considered

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
